\id XXC - The Text-Critical Greek New Testament 
\h APPENDIX C: BYZANTINE MANUSCRIPTS 
\toc1 Appendix C: Byzantine Manuscripts 
\toc2 Appendix C 
\toc3 App. C 
\mt1 APPENDIX C  
\mt2 BYZANTINE MANUSCRIPTS  
\ip The following lists of Byzantine manuscripts are used to determine the manuscript counts presented in the footnotes of this edition. A Byzantine manuscript is defined as any Greek manuscript that has at least a 90% alignment with the Byzantine text (as determined from the alignment data published in \it Text und Textwert\it*) and that is not a representative of the K\sup r\sup* manuscript family. (For the Catholic Epistles the threshold is 85% instead of 90%.) Please note that the \it Pericople Adulterae\it* and the book of Revelation are special cases that are treated separately. (See Appendices D, E, and F.)  
